  "prompt": "Why would I get a certified letter from the IRS?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why you might receive a certified letter from the IRS:\n\n1. Audit notification\n- You've been selected for a tax audit\n- The IRS needs additional documentation about your tax return\n\n2. Tax bill or notice of unpaid taxes\n- You owe additional taxes\n- There's a discrepancy in your tax return\n- You have an outstanding tax debt\n\n3. Request for information\n- Verification of income or deductions\n- Clarification about tax credits\n- Confirmation of personal details\n\n4. Urgent communication\n- Important tax-related matter that requires your immediate attention\n- Legal notice about tax issues\n\n5. Refund-related issues\n- Problem with a previously filed tax return\n- Questions about a tax refund\n\n6. Collection notices\n- Warning about potential tax liens\n- Notification of pending collection actions\n\n7. Identity verification\n- Confirming your identity to prevent tax fraud\n- Resolving potential identity theft issues\n\nWhen you receive a certified IRS letter, it's important to:\n- Open and read it carefully\n- Respond promptly\n- Follow the instructions\n- Contact the IRS if you have questions\n\nIf you're unsure about the letter's contents, consider consulting a tax professional.",
